### ===========================
### PORTFOLIO ENDPOINTS
### ===========================

### Create a new portfolio
### Expected: 201 Created
### Returns: portfolio object with id, name, description, createdDate, numberOfStocks=0, totalValue=0
POST http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Tech Stocks",
    "description": "My technology investments"
}

###

### Create a second portfolio
### Expected: 201 Created
### Returns: portfolio object with id=2
POST http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Growth Stocks",
    "description": "High growth investments"
}

###

### Get all portfolios
### Expected: 200 OK
### Returns: list of all portfolios with live stock values and totals
GET http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios

###

### Get one portfolio by id
### Expected: 200 OK
### Returns: single portfolio with all stocks and calculated totals
GET http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/1

###

### Get portfolio that does not exist
### Expected: 404 Not Found
### Returns: { "status": 404, "message": "Portfolio not found with id: 999" }
GET http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/999

###

### Update a portfolio
### Expected: 200 OK
### Returns: updated portfolio object with new name and description
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Tech Giants",
    "description": "Big tech investments"
}

###

### Try to create portfolio with empty name
### Expected: 400 Bad Request
### Returns: { "status": 400, "message": "Portfolio name cannot be empty" }
POST http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "",
    "description": "This should fail"
}

###

### Delete a portfolio (also deletes all its stocks)
### Expected: 204 No Content
### Returns: empty response
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/2

###

### ===========================
### STOCK ENDPOINTS
### ===========================

### Add Apple stock to portfolio 1
### Expected: 201 Created
### Returns: stock object with live price data from 12 Data
### Note: if AAPL already exists in portfolio 1 quantity will be added
POST http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/1/stocks
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "symbol": "AAPL",
    "quantity": 10,
    "purchasePrice": 189.50,
    "purchaseDate": "2024-01-15"
}

###

### Add Tesla stock to portfolio 1
### Expected: 201 Created
### Returns: stock object with live price data
POST http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/1/stocks
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "symbol": "TSLA",
    "quantity": 5,
    "purchasePrice": 220.00,
    "purchaseDate": "2024-01-20"
}

###

### Add Google stock to portfolio 1
### Expected: 201 Created
### Returns: stock object with live price data
POST http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/1/stocks
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "symbol": "GOOGL",
    "quantity": 3,
    "purchasePrice": 140.00,
    "purchaseDate": "2024-02-01"
}

###

### Try adding AAPL again to portfolio 1
### Expected: 201 OK
### Returns: existing AAPL stock with quantity increased (no duplicate created)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/1/stocks
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "symbol": "AAPL",
    "quantity": 5,
    "purchasePrice": 195.00,
    "purchaseDate": "2024-03-01"
}

###

### Get all stocks in portfolio 1
### Expected: 200 OK
### Returns: list of all stocks with live prices, profit/loss calculations
GET http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/1/stocks

###

### Get one stock by id
### Expected: 200 OK
### Returns: single stock with live price, current value, profit/loss
GET http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/1/stocks/1

###

### Get stock from wrong portfolio
### Expected: 404 Not Found
### Returns: { "status": 404, "message": "Stock does not belong to portfolio with id: 2" }
GET http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/2/stocks/1

###

### Get stock that does not exist
### Expected: 404 Not Found
### Returns: { "status": 404, "message": "Stock not found with id: 999" }
GET http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/1/stocks/999

###

### Update a stock quantity and purchase price
### Expected: 200 OK
### Returns: updated stock with recalculated profit/loss
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/1/stocks/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "quantity": 15,
    "purchasePrice": 189.50
}

###

### Try to add stock with negative quantity
### Expected: 400 Bad Request
### Returns: { "status": 400, "message": "Quantity must be greater than zero" }
POST http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/1/stocks
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "symbol": "AMZN",
    "quantity": -5,
    "purchasePrice": 150.00,
    "purchaseDate": "2024-01-15"
}

###

### Try to add stock with empty symbol
### Expected: 400 Bad Request
### Returns: { "status": 400, "message": "Stock symbol cannot be empty" }
POST http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/1/stocks
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "symbol": "",
    "quantity": 5,
    "purchasePrice": 150.00,
    "purchaseDate": "2024-01-15"
}

###

### Try to add stock with invalid symbol
### Expected: 400 Bad Request
### Returns: { "status": 400, "message": "Could not fetch name for symbol: INVALID" }
POST http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/1/stocks
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "symbol": "INVALID",
    "quantity": 5,
    "purchasePrice": 150.00,
    "purchaseDate": "2024-01-15"
}

###

### Delete a stock from portfolio
### Expected: 204 No Content
### Returns: empty response
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/4

###

### ===========================
### TREND ENDPOINTS
### ===========================

### Get stock trends - default 6 months
### Expected: 200 OK
### Returns: symbol, name and list of 6 monthly closing prices
GET http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/1/stocks/1/trends

###

### Get stock trends - 12 months
### Expected: 200 OK
### Returns: symbol, name and list of 12 monthly closing prices
GET http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/1/stocks/1/trends?months=12

###

### Get stock trends - 3 months
### Expected: 200 OK
### Returns: symbol, name and list of 3 monthly closing prices
GET http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/1/stocks/1/trends?months=3

###

### Get trends for stock that does not exist
### Expected: 404 Not Found
### Returns: { "status": 404, "message": "Stock not found with id: 999" }
GET http://localhost:8080/api/portfolios/1/stocks/999/trends